data.title: Philip I King Of Franks
data.text:
NamePhilip I King Of Franks, 28G Grandfather

Birth23 May 1052, Champagne-et-Fontaine, Aquitaine

Death29 Jul 1108, Melun, France

BurialSaint-Benoit-sur-Loire

MotherAnne Of Kiev (-1075)

Notes for Philip I King Of Franks

Co-reign may 23 1059 to August 4 1060

Solo-reign August 4 1060 to July 29 1108

Called the Amorous.

Managed to make a modest recovery from the low of his fathers reign.

Wikipedia:

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philip_I_of_France

Notes for Bertha Of Holland (Spouse 1)

After having 3 children with her husband Philip, she was repudiated. She then withdrew to the fortress of Montreul-sur-mer.

Notes for Bertrade De Montfort (Spouse 2)
